benchmark_data.query: What are the latest features in Python 3.12?
benchmark_data.expected_answer:
Python 3.12 introduces several key enhancements:

## Core Features
- More flexible f-string parsing with support for nested quotes, multi-line expressions, and comments[1][2]
- Support for isolated subinterpreters with separate Global Interpreter Locks[1]
- Enhanced error messages with better suggestions for typos and missing imports[1]
- Performance improvements delivering roughly 5% overall speed increase[1]

## Type System Improvements
- New type annotation syntax for generic classes[1]
- New @override decorator for methods[1]
- Improved TypedDict support for kwargs typing[2]

## Performance Optimizations
- Comprehension inlining, making list/dict/set comprehensions up to 2x faster[4]
- Support for the Linux perf profiler to report Python function names[1]
- New debugging/profiling API[1]

## Notable Deprecations
- Removed deprecated smtpd and distutils modules[1]
- Invalid backslash escape sequences now trigger SyntaxWarning instead of DeprecationWarning[1]

Citations:
[1] https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3127/
[2] https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-3-12-new-features/
[3] https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3120/
[4] https://www.infoworld.com/article/2338514/the-best-new-features-and-fixes-in-python-3-12.html
[5] https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3126/
[6] https://testdriven.io/blog/python312/

benchmark_data.query: What are the most widely adopted authentication standards for microservices in 2024?

- OAuth 2.0 with OpenID Connect for third-party authorization and federated identities

**Deployment Strategies:**
- Edge-Level Authorization using API Gateways for centralized authentication
- Service-Level Authorization for granular control over individual services

**Enterprise Solutions:**
- Centralized Identity Providers (IdPs) like Auth0 and Okta
- Mutual TLS (mTLS) for high-security service-to-service communication
